#: templates/stock/explanation.html:18
msgid "Price Earnings Ratio (PER)"
msgstr "株価収益率（PER）"

#: templates/stock/explanation.html:20
msgid "Indicates up to what multiple of earning per share the stock is bought."
msgstr "株価が1株当たり利益の何倍まで買われているかを表す。"

#: templates/stock/explanation.html:21
msgid ""
"A high PER indicates that the stock is overvalued, while a low PER indicates "
"that the stock is undervalued."
msgstr "PERが高ければ株価は割高、PERが低ければ株価は割安と判断される。"

#: templates/stock/explanation.html:25
msgid "Price Book-value Ratio (PBR)"
msgstr "株価純資産倍率（PBR）"

#: templates/stock/explanation.html:27
msgid "The ratio of the stock price to the value of the company's assets."
msgstr "株価が企業の持つ資産価値の何倍まで買われているかを表す。"

#: templates/stock/explanation.html:28
msgid ""
"A high PER indicates that the stock is overvalued relative to net assets, "
"while a low PER indicates that the stock is undervalued relative to net "
"assets."
msgstr ""
"この値が高いと純資産に比べて株価が高く買われているということであり、逆に低い"
"と 純資産に比べて株価が割安ということになる。"

#: templates/stock/explanation.html:32
msgid "Earnings Per Share (EPS)"
msgstr "1株当たり純利益（EPS）"

#: templates/stock/explanation.html:34
msgid ""
"This is the portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding "
"share of common stock, serving as a profitability indicator."
msgstr ""
"これは、企業の利益のうち、発行済み普通株式1株あたりに配分される部分であり、収"
